#. Tag: title
#: mobile.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mobile Computing with Linux"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mobile computing is mostly associated with laptops, PDAs and cellular phones (and the data exchange between them). Mobile hardware components, such as external hard disks, flash disks, or digital cameras, can be connected to laptops or desktop systems. A number of software components are involved in mobile computing scenarios and some applications are tailor-made for mobile use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: mobile.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Laptops"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "The hardware of laptops differs from that of a normal desktop system. This is because criteria like exchangeability, space requirements and power consumption must be taken into account. The manufacturers of mobile hardware have developed standard interfaces like Mini PCI and Mini PCIe that can be used to extend the hardware of laptops. The standards cover memory cards, network interface cards, and external hard disks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: mobile.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Power Conservation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "The inclusion of energy-optimized system components during laptop manufacturing contributes to their suitability for use without access to the electrical power grid. Their contribution to conservation of power is at least as important as that of the operating system. &productnamereg; supports various methods that control the power consumption of a laptop and have varying effects on the operating time under battery power. The following list is in descending order of contribution to power conservation:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Throttling the CPU speed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switching off the display illumination during pauses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manually adjusting the display illumination."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disconnecting unused, hotplug-enabled accessories (USB CD-ROM, external mouse, Wi-Fi, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spinning down the hard disk when idling."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detailed background information about power management in &productname; is provided in <xref linkend=\"cha.power-mgmt\"/> . <!--<phrase os=\"sled\">For desktop specific power management, see <xref linkend=\"sec.gnomeuser.start.power_mgmt\"/> on how to use the &gnome; Power Manager.</phrase>-->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: mobile.xml:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Integration in Changing Operating Environments"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Your system needs to adapt to changing operating environments when used for mobile computing. Many services depend on the environment and the underlying clients must be reconfigured. &productname; handles this task for you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: mobile.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Integrating a Mobile Computer in an Existing Environment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "The services affected in the case of a laptop commuting back and forth between a small home network and an office network are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: mobile.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "This includes IP address assignment, name resolution, Internet connectivity and connectivity to other networks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: mobile.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Printing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "A current database of available printers and an available print server must be present, depending on the network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: mobile.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-Mail and Proxies"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "As with printing, the list of the corresponding servers must be current."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: mobile.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "X (Graphical Environment)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "If your laptop is temporarily connected to a projector or an external monitor, different display configurations must be available."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; offers several ways of integrating laptops into existing operating environments:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: mobile.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "&nm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: mobile.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "&nm; is especially tailored for mobile networking on laptops. It provides a means to easily and automatically switch between network environments or different types of networks such as mobile broadband (such as GPRS, EDGE, or 3G), wireless LAN, and Ethernet. &nm; supports WEP and WPA-PSK encryption in wireless LANs. It also supports dial-up connections. The &gnome; desktop includes a front-end for &nm;. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec.nm.configure\"/> ."
msgstr ""

